taxonomy: Bags, Wallets and Luggage/Travel Accessories/Swiss Army Knives/Victorinox Swiss Card Black Swiss Army Knife (0.7333.T3)
review: It's a very useful thing to have around. I bought it for me wife and she always keeps it in h er purse. You never know when you might need it for some small job, cutting a loose thread from a dress, open a letter, tighten a screw, pick a splinter from under a nail... the list is endless. The compact form factor is a big added bonus.Really well thought out and beautifully executed.
Bought this and i have to say the quality of the product is amazing.
The knife and the scissors are just too sharp and most importantly this just snugs into your wallet with no issues.
I can now carry this anywhere without any issues.
Its really card like stuff will useful only when you run out of your ammunition and you want to do something. Its last hope kind of thing. Don't expect it will give you ease of work and all that.
Overall fair price and stuff which req. one PEN, KNIFE, RULER,LIGHT, SCREW DRIVER And one pin needal

Awesome stuff to keep in your wallet everyday! bought it on Diwali discount for just 931 INR and its an awesome tool for EDC. So far I have used all the items (in real situations). The drawback is the Pen and the LED. LED is so small and not powerful, probably for that single battery. Again it is not meant to be a torch :p if it was it would have been bulkier and won't fit in your wallet!
Pen is not that Good, you will need to struggle a bit :/
Brilliant mini toolkit to carry around in the wallet.  Great conversation piece in parties too, took it out to cut a packet of snacks last evening & friends were examining it for a while!
This Swiss card has almost everything you'd ever need when it comes to an emergency.
And it has a touch of premium finishing to it, too!
I took a star because it's a tad bit thick - still fits in my wallet though.
